Rating: 3
Super easy, just the thing in summer. This took no time to prepare and was tasty, although not the most "wow" fish dish I ever made. I think the fact that I made aioli from scratch was critical to its success (the dish needed generous dollops of aioli to jazz it up, so homemade was critical).

Rating: 3
Easy and delicious... am always surprised how long eggplant takes to grill -- be patient! Skewered the cherry tomatoes for easy grilling. Also cut up a red pepper. Used garden-fresh herbs (thyme, tarragon, basil, oregano & rosemary) along with some fennel seeds, and drizzled in some 18 yr (syrupy) balsamic. Would definitely make again. Looking forward to my lunch of leftovers. Don't forget the aioli (1/2 cup of mayo, 2 tbs olive oil, 1/4 tsp salt, 2 cloves of garlic, and 1 tbs lemon juice).

